    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I need help writing a rejection email. We had a candidate, Marcus, who made it all the way to the final interview for our Senior Dev role here in Austin. He's really talented and had great technical skills, but we decided to go with someone who had a bit more experience with our specific cloud architecture. I want the email to be professional and kind because he was a great guy, but we need to be firm that the decision is final. Can you draft something?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Subject: Your Application for the Senior Dev Position – Thank You\n\nDear Marcus,\n\nI hope this message finds you well. We sincerely appreciate the time you invested in the interview process answering our questions regarding your skills and experience.\n\nAfter careful consideration, I regret to inform you that we have chosen to move forward with a candidate whose experience more closely aligns with our specific cloud architecture needs for the Senior Dev role here in Austin.\n\nWe were truly impressed with your proficiency, active problem solving, and enthusiasm for your career. We wish you all the best on your future endeavors and hope you find a role that presents new challenges and opportunities for your talent.\n\nThank you once again for considering Austin as your next career milestone. We appreciate having you in our network and wish you every success in the future.\n\nBest regards,\n\n[Your Name]\n[Your Position]\n[Company Name]",
